issue.title: Improve actions discoverability and UX on file page

labels.name: needs-design
labels.description: Design requests - add to 'design priorities' project, add a deadline, if possible..

issue.body:
Users do not search to search alone, they search to perform actions. Sourcegraph allows users to perform key actions on the file page, but the design of these moments has several usability problems that hinders their discovery and use. 

This change:
* Moves lessor used icons to a dropdown where expansion can occur 
* Labels the key actions at the top level

If this change is successful, it will promote additional use of these key functions and position Sourcegraph as a tool that helps users perform key actions in their workflow. 


### Before
![image](https://github.com/sourcegraph/sourcegraph/assets/539268/2d7e7957-96cb-4f64-b528-0f6675c0ebf3)

### After (Initial design)
![image](https://github.com/sourcegraph/sourcegraph/assets/539268/44b9189c-d42b-4c4d-8252-197857a59e9f)



## Design process

  - Estimate: Three days
  - Weighting factors:
    - LOW risk
    - HIGH clarity

  ### Discover
  - [ ] Existing customer feedback - Link
  - [x] Analytics - [Link](https://app.amplitude.com/analytics/sourcegraph/dashboard/tw6ulwty)

  ### Define
  - [x] GitHub issue

  ### Design
  - [x] High fidelity design using design system - [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/skTkU7PPWCvH2SAlP9GYtC/Search-Suite-Q4-UX-work?type=design&node-id=3-10575&mode=design&t=y2Jf1OOvONfSbnXq-0)
  - [x] Prototype - [Figma](https://www.figma.com/proto/skTkU7PPWCvH2SAlP9GYtC/Search-Suite-Q4-UX-work?page-id=3%3A10575&type=design&node-id=215-7295&viewport=550%2C3470%2C0.48&t=MVubXCTOg8B28ZO3-1&scaling=min-zoom&starting-point-node-id=215%3A7295&mode=design)
  - [x] Prod team and design team review

  ### Testing
  - [x] Hallway testing - [Link](https://sourcegraph.slack.com/archives/C05D629GWJK/p1698255200679059)
  - [ ] Usertesting.com task-based evaluation - Link

  ### Deliver
  - [x] Loom - [Link](https://www.loom.com/share/a1cf5b62f44b4c24945791aa2fc16da8)
  - [ ] QA - Link

  ### Measure
  - [x] Metrics defined in the Figma file ([i](https://handbook.sourcegraph.com/departments/product-engineering/product/design/metrics/defining-metrics/)) - Link
  - [ ] Followup task will analyze metrics to ensure successful completion - Link

comment.body:
I think we're ready to go on this @sourcegraph/code-search 

Please review the [prototype](https://www.figma.com/proto/skTkU7PPWCvH2SAlP9GYtC/Search-Suite-Q4-UX-work?page-id=3%3A10575&type=design&node-id=215-7295&viewport=550%2C3470%2C0.48&t=MVubXCTOg8B28ZO3-1&scaling=min-zoom&starting-point-node-id=215%3A7295&mode=design) and [designs](https://www.figma.com/file/skTkU7PPWCvH2SAlP9GYtC/Search-Suite-Q4-UX-work?type=design&node-id=3-10575&mode=design&t=y2Jf1OOvONfSbnXq-0).

If anything is unclear, let us know before you start implementation.

pull_request.title: use swc instead of babel for faster bazel typescript transpilation
pull_request.body:
swc is a very fast TypeScript transpiler.

Instead of using Babel for TypeScript transpilation in Bazel, we now use swc, which is much faster. We still use Babel in Jest (for tests), but in the future we intend to move away from Jest.

See https://docs.aspect.build/rulesets/aspect_rules_ts/docs/transpiler#swc-recommended for more information about using swc in Bazel, and https://swc.rs/ for general information about swc.

## Test plan

CI
